      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAW ALLESANDRA (2) has some solid form under her belt and proved too strong last time to win by 0.8 lengths at this track in a handy 22.40 beating Curdievale Rhode. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and two minor placings to her credit. In great recent form and expected to measure up again. PAW BASTOW (8) was quickly into stride and burnt early from out wide where she gave a sight, finishing third (22.96) and beaten 4 lengths over 400m at Geelong. Expected to feature again. BELAIR BLUE (1) stalked the lead from the inside draw then took over turning and burst clear to score (23.12) at Mt Gambier in a Grade 6 over 400m. Solid formlines coming through his last run. Form should stack up. CHALK AND CHEESE (4) gets a chance to redeem an unplaced effort here last start.",
